title: Music Companies Sue Twitter Over Alleged Copyright Violations
description: Publishers representing thousands of artists are seeking more than $250 million in damages for use of music in tweets.

title: AI Regulation Is Almost Here in Europe
description: The European Union’s Parliament voted to push forward draft legislation that is positioned to be the West’s first comprehensive set of AI regulations.

title: EU Says It May Seek Breakup of Google's Ad-Tech Business
description: The move means Europe is joining the U.S.’s antitrust assault on Google’s ad-tech business, potentially setting up a protracted battle.

title: The 'Taxi Prince' Is Taking on Uber---and Winning
description: Uber has been outmaneuvered in one of the world’s largest taxi markets by the man known as Japan’s taxi prince.

title: Nvidia Rides AI Boom to Become Latest U.S. $1 Trillion Company
description: The chip company ended trading Tuesday with a valuation of more than $1 trillion, becoming the seventh U.S. company to reach that status.
